By Sept. 17, 2015, 4:05 p.m. 

Police are appealing for information after a report that a 15-year-old girl had been sexually assaulted by three teenage boys at a party in the lower Blue Mountains. 

On the evening of Saturday August 15 the girl was at a party at Bellevue Road in Faulconbridge, police said. 

She left later that night to attend a small gathering of teenagers at a home in Crane Street, Springwood, where the alleged attack took place. 

The girl was sexually assaulted by three boys believed to be about 17-years-old, police were told. 

Officers attached to the Blue Mountains Local Area Command were notified and established Strike Force Downe to investigate the alleged aggravated sexual assault. 

The girl was not taken to hospital. 

Police would not say whether there were adults at home at the time of the incident, or if the girl knew all the teenagers at the small gathering while their investigations were under way. 

Detectives are appealing to anyone with information, or anyone who was at both parties to come forward. 

Contact Blue Mountains police on 02 4751 0299 or Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000. 

